Hon. Hammed Idowu D. Tijani (H.I.D), chairman of Ojokoro Local Council Development Area (LCDA) has undertaken a giant stride to­wards grassroots development when he presented N3.827 billion budget for 2022 fiscal year to the council leg­islators on February 15, 2022. The budget tagged, ‘Budget of Continued Transformation’, was said to represent an increase of 10% over that of year 2021. The budget was received by the council leader, Hon. Tunde Olalekan Oyekunle, at the local council legis­lative chamber. Osun Guber: Let’s Close Ranks And Eschew Bitterness,… Corruption Charges: Nto Floors ICPC In Court, Demands Apology In his speech, Tijani said that apart from education, health, and security, priority is being given to Non-current Assets and Social Ser­vice Expenditure (SSE), like Agri­culture, Rural and Social Develop­ment Sector, Women Affairs, and Poverty Alleviation Programmes, etc, which formed 40% of the bud­get as directed by the Lagos State government. “We have resolved to pursue vig­orously the execution of far reach­ing socio-economic projects with a view of making life more meaning­ful to the good people of the LCDA,” he stated.